dismissalText.commentary: Nishan Madushka c Root b Woakes 4 (16b 0x4 0x6 27m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: another shot in anger, another one goes! That's a really poor shot, so soon after the wicket. It was a gullible outswinger, very full, swinging out of the hand, begging to be driven, but Madushka's footwork couldn't match his ambitions. A simple snick straight into Root's breadbasket at first slip, who clings on in the heel of his palms. This is going south very rapidly all of a sudden

dismissalText.commentary: Angelo Mathews lbw b Woakes 0 (5b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: No stroke offered, up goes the finger! Oh my, a terrible misjudgement, or is it? Mathews reviews, maybe hoping it was going over the top. He certainly must have been leaving on length as that was too tight to off stump initially... angled in initially, nipping back further, clipping the top of the bails! Disaster for Sri Lanka, the ball is talking now too as the lacquer comes off the ball. Buckle up!

dismissalText.commentary: Dinesh Chandimal lbw b Shoaib Bashir 17 (40b 2x4 0x6 73m) SR: 42.5

dismissalComment.html: Chandimal done in by a daisy cutter! One had kept low in the previous over, but this one barely got off the ground! It was back of a length, pitching outside off and turning back in. But it kept so low that Chandimal was struck near his ankle! Chandimal reviews probably in disbelief more than anything else, but it's three reds and he must go. With less than 10 minutes to lunch Sri Lanka have lost their fifth
